@Rapid_Pkz wrote:

who cares if its leeched most people do… :mad:[br][br][size=1]Posted on: February 16, 2009, 11:00:42 pm[/size][hr][quote=“dannyboii06, post:1, topic:262647”][quote author=jc22493 link=topic=346601.msg2670152#msg2670152 date=1234794693]

if we cant edit it then how did the Rapid Pkz dude make hiself a owner or admin or wateva

You do that in your Login class.
[/quote]

You can use the login class, but if you change this after you’ve created the account, it will null the account.

Basically, right click on the character file (NAME.dat) and select “Open with”.

Choose wordpad, or notepad (On some systems, there has been reports of words changing to symbols when using notepad).

Change “rights = 0” to one of the following:

[ul]0 = Regular member
1 = Moderator
2 = Administrator[/ul]

Note: There is no rights above 2 because there is no rank above Jagex Moderator in RuneScape. Just the way Jagex have programmed it.

Any problems PM me.

This is pretty much a 99.999% leach (Yes it’s spelt right) from Berky’s source.[/quote]
